To compile, type :
./configure
make

Useful configure options :
 --enable-gnutls : compile with gnutls support used for secure connections
 --enable-filter : enable data filtering (see doc/filter.conf)

Copy ./doc/example.conf to ./child.conf, and edit it
If you compiled with filter support, you can copy ./doc/filter.conf to ./filter.conf and edit it
Type ./child -c to create mysql tables.
Then, you can start child by typing ./child
